Convert to Weak Greiback Normal Form

It is not difficult to see that if we are able to achieve

, where is a terminal and can be any string, then we will be able to further convert it to the strong Greibach Normal Form mentioned at the begining of this note. The above form is called Weak Normal Form. As long as the first symbol is a terminal, we eliminate the possibility of left recursion. To achieve this, we need to introduce more “notation tricks” to represent production rules as matrix operations.
